{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":94543,"duration_api_ms":94022,"num_turns":3,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"b8efb220-2c22-446a-8f3c-884e6470dfda","total_cost_usd":0.43131010000000014,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":36370,"cache_read_input_tokens":67873,"output_tokens":1705,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":36370,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":1705,"cacheReadInputTokens":67873,"cacheCreationInputTokens":36370,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.303894,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":54,"outputTokens":5053,"cacheReadInputTokens":583821,"cacheCreationInputTokens":34972,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.1274161,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"rulings":[{"amendment_id":"fr-17-3303d1eb","decision":"reject","rationale":"The amendment's premise is factually incorrect. It claims `active_child.wait()` is 'an OS I/O operation that won't trigger auto-advance,' but inspection of ManagedChild::wait() (process_backend.rs:431-455) reveals a polling loop: `child.try_wait()` (non-blocking) followed by `tokio::time::sleep(CHILD_WAIT_POLL_INTERVAL)` (a 10ms timer sleep). Similarly, `confirm_teardown()` (line 1528-1537) wraps the same polling wait in `tokio::time::timeout()`. All pending futures in this test are timer-based, so `start_paused = true` with auto-advance works correctly by design — not as a fragile coupling to Tokio internals. Reviewer 2 correctly identified this: the ManagedChild was explicitly designed with poll-based waiting (comment at lines 436-437 explains this is intentional to allow lock-free cancellation). Adding a comment based on the amendment's false premise would be misleading. The test is sound as written."}],"summary":"Rejected the sole disputed amendment (fr-17-3303d1eb). Code inspection proves the amendment's core claim is wrong: ManagedChild::wait() uses timer-based polling (try_wait + tokio::time::sleep), not blocking OS I/O. With start_paused=true, all pending futures are timer-driven, making auto-advance work by intentional design rather than fragile Tokio-internal coupling. Reviewer 2's rejection was correct; the planner and Reviewer 1 accepted without verifying the wait() implementation."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"699d2154-3f91-4cf2-8d6f-b536052c571a"}
